---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Viking Wine Cooler Repair | Southern California | VWUI + VCWB Column";
const description = "Viking wine cooler repair SoCal, VWUI/VWUO undercounter + VCWB column integration. Viking Professional 7 Series suite. Middleby Greenwood MS. $89 dx.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/viking-wine-cooler-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Which Viking wine cooler models are common in LA luxury kitchens?",
    a: "Viking's wine cooler lineup centers on two main architectures. <b>VWUI / VWUO undercounter wine coolers</b>, 15-inch + 24-inch undercounter-format units installed at kitchen islands, butler's pantries, or secondary-zone positions; compressor-based, dual-zone variants available. <b>VCWB column integration</b>, full-height built-in column wine storage pairing with Virtuoso 7 Series refrigerator + freezer columns for matched-column luxury suites. LA install concentration mirrors Viking Professional kitchen geography: Bel Air + Beverly Hills custom luxury with full Viking suite, Pacific Palisades + Malibu canyon/coastal estates, Manhattan Beach + Palos Verdes coastal, Pasadena + San Marino established luxury. Panel-ready integrated variants accept custom cabinetry for seamless kitchen integration. Legacy Viking wine cooler platforms (Designer Series pre-current generation) continue in active service via Middleby parts distribution."
  },
  {
    q: "Viking wine cooler not maintaining temperature, diagnostic order?",
    a: "Standard Viking wine cooler diagnostic sequence: (1) verify ambient temperature and door seal, compressor-based units should maintain 55°F regardless of room temperature, but failed gaskets cause warm-air infiltration that looks like compressor failure; door gasket $280–$380. (2) Condenser cleaning, front-mount condenser dust accumulation is the #1 maintenance failure; deep clean $120–$180 often resolves without parts. (3) Temperature sensor check, NTC drift at 5-8 year mark per section; swap $240–$320. (4) Evaporator fan motor, airflow-dependent cooling per zone; motor swap $320–$460. (5) Compressor start relay + capacitor $260–$400 first-line before compressor work. (6) Compressor replacement $900–$1,400 including refrigerant recharge. Viking wine cooler service economics run at the upper-luxury tier reflecting Middleby OEM parts pricing. Parts lead time 4-6 days typical via Middleby Greenwood MS distribution."
  },
  {
    q: "Does Viking wine cooler coordinate with Viking Professional suite service?",
    a: "Yes, this matters for LA luxury households running full Viking Professional kitchens. Viking's residential portfolio (refrigerator + range + stove + cooktop + oven + wall oven + ice maker + trash compactor + wine cooler + bbq grill) flows through the same Middleby Greenwood MS parts distribution network, which means multi-appliance service visits across a Viking Professional suite coordinate efficiently. Wine cooler service shares parts-chain efficiency with other Viking service calls, if you've had Viking service before, the channel is already familiar to our techs. See our Viking service family: <a href='/brands/viking-refrigerator-repair/'>refrigerator</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-built-in-refrigerator-repair/'>built-in refrigerator</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-stove-repair/'>stove</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-range-repair/'>range</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-cooktop-repair/'>cooktop</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-oven-repair/'>oven</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-ice-maker-repair/'>ice maker</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-trash-compactor-repair/'>trash compactor</a> · <a href='/brands/viking-bbq-grill-repair/'>bbq grill</a>."
  },
  {
    q: "Dual-zone Viking wine cooler, one zone working, other not?",
    a: "Dual-zone wine cooler differential failure points to zone-specific components rather than shared compressor failure. Diagnostic order: (1) zone evaporator fan motor, each zone has its own fan circulating cooled air; fan failure on one zone eliminates active cooling to that compartment; swap $320–$460. (2) Zone temperature sensor, NTC drift in one zone causing control logic to misread + under-cool or over-cool; sensor $240–$320. (3) Zone damper mechanism (on zone-separated airflow architectures), stuck damper cuts airflow to one zone while the other continues normally; service $260–$380. (4) Door gasket on the failing zone, compression loss allows warm air infiltration; gasket $280–$380. (5) Rare: zone-specific control board on newer electronic generations $440–$640. Viking's Middleby parts chain supports dual-zone component replacement with typical 4-6 day LA-authorized lead on common zone components."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Viking wine cooler repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Common Viking wine cooler service bands: condenser deep clean $120–$180 (annual maintenance); temperature sensor NTC $240–$320; water inlet valve (rare, some integrated variants) $260–$360; evaporator fan motor $320–$460 per zone; defrost heater + thermostat $320–$460; door gasket $280–$380 per section; compressor start relay + capacitor $260–$400; compressor replacement $900–$1,400 including refrigerant recharge; main control board $440–$660; display board $320–$480; panel-overlay gasket (integrated VCWB) $320–$460; full refresh package $800–$1,200 (sensor + gasket + fan + cleaning). Viking wine cooler service runs 15-20% above mainstream wine cooler brands reflecting Middleby OEM parts. Parts lead 4-6 days typical via Middleby Greenwood MS on common components."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Viking wine cooler and Viking built-in refrigerator service?",
    a: "Wine cooler and built-in refrigerator are distinct product categories with different engineering specs even under shared Viking brand. Wine cooler (this page) = 55°F wine storage temperature range, humidity control for cork preservation, single-zone or dual-zone temperature management, specialty wine-rack interior, UV-protected glass doors on most models, compressor-based or thermoelectric architecture. <a href='/brands/viking-built-in-refrigerator-repair/'>Viking built-in refrigerator</a> = 37-40°F fresh food storage + 0°F freezer, standard refrigerator + freezer interior, column or side-by-side architecture, stainless or panel-ready integrated finish. Both service via Middleby Greenwood MS parts chain; both require front-ventilated built-in service access. For matched luxury column suite (refrigerator column + freezer column + wine column), we coordinate multi-column service visits efficiently through the shared Middleby channel. See also <a href='/services/wine-cooler-repair/'>wine cooler service hub</a> + <a href='/services/built-in-refrigerator-repair/'>built-in refrigerator service hub</a>."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Viking Wine Cooler Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Viking Wine Cooler Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Viking wine cooler repair across Southern California, LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. VWUI / VWUO 15-inch + 24-inch undercounter wine coolers + VCWB column integration with Virtuoso 7 Series + Professional 7 Series Viking suite. Middleby Greenwood MS since 2002. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Viking", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/viking/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Viking Wine Cooler Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Viking wine cooler service? Same-day across all 5 SoCal counties:</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › <a href="/brands/viking/">Viking</a> › Wine Cooler Repair</div>
    <h1>Viking Wine Cooler Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Viking's wine cooler line covers two main luxury architectures. <b>VWUI / VWUO undercounter wine coolers</b> install as 15-inch + 24-inch undercounter units at kitchen islands + butler's pantries + secondary-zone positions; compressor-based with single-zone or dual-zone temperature management + UV-protected glass doors + specialty wine-rack interiors. <b>VCWB column integration</b> pairs with Virtuoso 7 Series refrigerator + freezer columns for matched-column luxury suites in full-Viking-Professional kitchens. Middleby Greenwood MS parts chain (since Middleby's 2002 Viking acquisition) delivers 4-6 day typical LA-authorized service lead on common components. LA install concentration: Bel Air + Beverly Hills custom Viking Professional kitchens, Pacific Palisades + Malibu estate installs, Pasadena + San Marino established luxury. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>VWUI + VWUO undercounter</b>, 15" + 24" single/dual-zone</li>
      <li><b>VCWB column integration</b>, matched Virtuoso 7 Series suite</li>
      <li><b>Middleby Greenwood MS</b>, Viking Professional suite parts chain</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Common Viking wine cooler failures our techs see in LA</h2>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Temperature drift, condenser + gasket + sensor</h3><p>Sequential diagnostic. Condenser clean $120–$180; gasket $280–$380; NTC sensor $240–$320. Most resolve without compressor work.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Dual-zone differential, zone fan or sensor</h3><p>One zone working + other not = zone-specific component. Fan motor $320–$460 or sensor $240–$320 per zone.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Compressor start issues, relay first</h3><p>Start relay + capacitor $260–$400 before escalating to compressor. Many 'compressor failure' calls resolve at relay.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Door seal compression loss</h3><p>10-15 yr gasket compression → warm air infiltration → excessive cycling. Per-section $280–$380 replacement.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Panel-overlay service (VCWB integrated)</h3><p>Integrated VCWB column accepts custom cabinetry panels. Panel-protection discipline during service; interior work access preferred.</p></div>
    <div class="fail-block"><h3>Vibration increase, wine collection protection</h3><p>Aged-wine sediment sensitivity. Compressor mount deterioration at 10-15 yr; isolation-mount replacement $240–$380.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Viking wine cooler repair typically costs</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Condenser deep clean</td><td>$120 – $180</td><td>Annual maintenance</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Temperature sensor NTC</td><td>$240 – $320</td><td>Per zone</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Evaporator fan motor</td><td>$320 – $460</td><td>Per zone</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door gasket</td><td>$280 – $380</td><td>Per section</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Compressor start relay + capacitor</td><td>$260 – $400</td><td>First-line diagnostic</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Compressor replacement</td><td>$900 – $1,400</td><td>Refrigerant recharge included</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Compressor isolation mounts</td><td>$240 – $380</td><td>Vibration reduction</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board</td><td>$440 – $660</td><td>Electronic generations</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Display board</td><td>$320 – $480</td><td>UI + error display</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Panel-overlay gasket (VCWB)</td><td>$320 – $460</td><td>Integrated variants</td></tr>
      <tr><td>full refresh (10-15 yr)</td><td>$800 – $1,200</td><td>Gasket + sensor + fan + clean</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/viking-refrigerator-repair/">Viking refrigerator</a> · <a href="/brands/viking-built-in-refrigerator-repair/">Viking built-in refrigerator</a> · <a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove</a> · <a href="/services/wine-cooler-repair/">Wine cooler service hub</a> · <a href="/services/built-in-refrigerator-repair/">Built-in refrigerator service hub</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Service areas, where our Viking wine cooler calls come from</h2>
    <div class="area-grid">
      <div><h4>Bel Air + Beverly Hills</h4><p><a href="/beverly-hills/">Beverly Hills</a> · Bel Air · Holmby Hills</p></div>
      <div><h4>Pacific Palisades + Brentwood</h4><p>Pacific Palisades · <a href="/brentwood/">Brentwood</a></p></div>
      <div><h4>Malibu + coastal luxury</h4><p><a href="/malibu/">Malibu</a> · Manhattan Beach · Palos Verdes</p></div>
      <div><h4>Hollywood Hills</h4><p>Hollywood Hills · Laurel Canyon</p></div>
      <div><h4>Pasadena + San Marino</h4><p><a href="/pasadena/">Pasadena</a> · San Marino · La Cañada</p></div>
      <div><h4>OC luxury</h4><p>Newport Coast · Corona del Mar · <a href="/irvine/">Irvine</a></p></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Related Viking + wine cooler pages</h2>
    <ul class="related-links">
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-refrigerator-repair/">Viking refrigerator repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-built-in-refrigerator-repair/">Viking built-in refrigerator →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-stove-repair/">Viking stove repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-range-repair/">Viking range repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/viking-ice-maker-repair/">Viking ice maker repair →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/wine-cooler-repair/">Wine cooler service hub →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/services/wine-cellar-repair/">Wine cellar service hub (walk-in scale) →</a></li>
      <li><a href="/brands/sub-zero-wine-cooler-repair/">Sub-Zero wine cooler (luxury alt) →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Viking wine cooler repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Viking wine cooler down? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 0 0 10px; color: var(--black); }
  h4 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .fail-block { background: #fff; border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px 22px; margin: 16px 0; }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; }
  .area-grid > div { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; border-radius: 6px; }
  .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; } .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .related-links a { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; } .related-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } h2 { font-size: 1.45rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
